snippet.textDisplay:
Ben, Your videos are encouraging. I am an American from Arizona. Currently in Huludao China, Liaoning Province with my chinese wife visiting family. Arrived mid January. Huludao is about 1000 miles northeast of Wuhan. I am sure you know flights to and from China have been suspended most or all airlines with this lockdown, so we are not going anywhere anytime soon.

Things here in Huludao are nothing compared to what you must deal with in Wuhan. I seen the vacant streets in your video. I have been to Huludao 6 Times over several years and have never seen it like this, like a ghost town. I loved the Q&A video and that brings me to a couple questions. I see you wear 2 masks. Price gouging of pharmaceuticals is out of control here. One example is the price of medical masks has gone up 2000% and in some pharmacies even more. Most pharmacies are out of stock. Can i assume Wuhan is as bad or worse? Are you anywhere near the 2 hospitals they are quickly building?

I want to thank you. You are truly an inspiration to me as a visitor to china. I am sure/hope others who viewed your videos feel as i do.

Many will agree that it's terribly scary to see such a modern day plague disperse it venom amongst the nation's once again.
As it spreads it's deliberate nastiness from people to people,
delivering pain and suffering, we find ourselves wondering, were did it come from, where will it go, can we fight it? Sometimes we have a moment of pondering, is this thing man made, maybe to aid in population control, or is it simply a part of this world's sick state of commerce, to create a supply and demand. One would hope that to create a Corona plague and than supply it's kryptonite was not the masterplan, simply to line the pockets of the great merchant. Would it be terrible to think such a thing, and would this not destroy our faith in those of whom pull on the proverbial puppet strings. It certainly causes us to question our moral state in these days of darkness. But should we be surprised is the bigger question?
Or does all fingers and toes point to the tree climbing monkey and(or) the nocturnal tree hanging bat???? I don't know....
An ancient king of wisdom once pinned inspired words for Ecclesiastes, "man has dominated man to his harm" and another quote by an inspired Jeremiah stated, " It does not belong to man who is walking even to direct his step" or as the prophetic Israelite, Moses once wrote "Consequently, Jehovah(God) saw that man’s wickedness was great on the earth and that every inclination of the thoughts of his heart was only bad all the time"
So it's stands to reason, to have such thinking is certainly not a stretch of the imagination, but does it have validity in this case, who knows, again there's that shadow of a doubt that may cause us to wonder.
For those who use God's word as a solemn resource, are probably familiar with the book written by John, pinned for our time, speaking of this revelation, "And I saw, and look! a pale horse, and the one seated on it had the name Death. And the Grave was closely following him"-"and with deadly plague". This scripture clearly identifies our day being characterized by great plagues. So is this the nature of our near and far sighted existence? Will that very same revelation speaks to the solution to man's problem.
Revelation 21:3,4,5 offers a great hope "Look! The tent of God is with mankind, and he will reside with them, and they will be his people. And God himself will be with them. And he will wipe out every tear from their eyes, and death will be no more, neither will mourning nor outcry nor pain be anymore. The former things have passed away. And the One seated on the throne said: “Look! I am making all things new.
So the prophetic words of the Holy Scriptures doesn't just highlight the issues of humanity, but it also brings attention to the remedy of those issues, or for lack of better word the vaccine, that being, Jehovah God's Kingdom. This Godly Kingdom government will soon end all of mankind's problems. We can have trust and faith in Jehovah God, that this will take place as the scriptures say, no words will leave his mouth without results, as we know God does not lie.
So to all that struggle with the unknown in regard to our future, be confident that better times are to come, this pale horse will soon be stoped and it's rider will be final kicked off, and done away with.
For further encouragement on your future, please visit JW.org and your will find many of your questions answered. Here you can also request a personal bible study that can certainly assist you in gaining true confidents in our future. :)

snippet.textDisplay:
My wife and I are also in China, we have it around us and it grows more each day, doctors and nurses also have the problem. we are in one of the Suzhou districts, her parents are in Shanghai the problems are also there, I am not too worried about, we have money here, the biggest concern is the health sector for overseas people like myself, it is very very expensive no acc here, and I do disagree with Ben's comment on food, food here is not cheap maybe in his area but for us, its a lot more expensive than New Zealand. but if he is a teacher his income will be high so there for china is cheap for overseas people working and if you want to spend up you can live very comfortably and great, but unfortunately for everyday Chinese folk China is not so the case.
The hardest part is transportation, at the moment this is not good we can not get to shanghai even if we wanted to, I have seen no local busses or taxis running let alone any long-distance busses, so the worry is more with Her parents than ourselves, my family want us home, the thing is even tho we meet in New Zealand and lived a long time in New Zealand and came here two years ago, now the kids are not so dependent on us, the risk sounds like the government here in China can refuse her leaving and this has been the case for a few couples so it means staying with your loved one or leaving them behind like some coward, so do I leave without my wife or stay with her?
I also have commitments back home but she also does here, and hers are also mine. talk about being in a pickle.
I had to go shopping today as our food and water was very low, and have taken notices in the drop in fresh food in the supermarkets, a lot of it was really really bad. but you can't worry about it or you will go mad, brought what I could and people were pushing as if it were their last shop, keeping contact with family and trying not to listen to the world news makes it feel better lols.

snippet.textDisplay: According to WHO, a quarter of a million to half a million people die of flu every year. Scaling those figures, one would expect 4000 to 8000 deaths from flu every month in China. So far there have been around 230 deaths in about 10000 confirmed cases, most of whom were elderly or had pre-existing medical conditions. There is at most 2% fatality rate, which will probably drop once all infected cases are known. 80% of cases have had mild symptoms. There is nothing unusual about this flu outbreak at all, it has posed no significant health risk beyond that of ordinary flu. There is no rational explanation for the extreme reaction and panic we are seeing.
